{"author_date": "2026-06-11T15:36:27Z", "author_login": "haakon-e", "commit_date": "2026-06-11T16:47:57Z", "committer_login": "haakon-e", "message": "feat(P3): faster, type-stable 2M+P3 collision path; bump to 0.37\n\nAdvance the 2M<->P3 collision integrals on several fronts; the resulting\nBulkMicrophysicsTendencies API change drives the 0.37 bump.\n\n- Gauss-Legendre quadrature, opt-in: add GaussLegendre{FT, N}, built ONCE\n  at parameter construction (FastGaussQuadrature computes the nodes in\n  Float64; converted to FT and stored as NTuples on P3IceParams), so the\n  hot loop only reads a precomputed isbits rule -- GPU-safe, any order.\n  Selected at the BMT quadrature site via quadrature_order; ChebyshevGauss\n  remains the default. As cheap as and substantially more accurate than\n  ChebyshevGauss at matched order on the smooth P3 integrands.\n\n- Closed-form rain-inner liquid-ice collision integral (N, M): exact\n  incomplete-gamma reduction of the rain {N, M} inner integral --\n  velocity-crossover split, a shared gamma_inc_moment kernel, reusing\n  CO.particle_terminal_velocity. Solver plus in-suite tests. The inner\n  piece_NM helper takes its working float types as arguments: capturing a\n  computed Type in a closure stores it as a bare DataType, which widens\n  the return to Tuple{Any,Any} under Julia <= 1.11 inference.\n\n- Keep the collision path in the working float type: pin the collision\n  quadrature and cloud-bound helpers to the data eltype so the Float32/GPU\n  P3 integrals do not leak Float64 -- pin SB2006 cloud bounds to eltype(q),\n  and migrate the ice-deposition call to the upstream conv_q_vap_to_q_icl\n  split. No Float64 behaviour change.\n\n- Guard the unlimited rain PDF against non-positive number/mass: broaden\n  the degenerate-input short-circuit in\n  pdf_rain_parameters(::RainParticlePDF_SB2006_notlimited, ...) from both-\n  zero (&&) to either-below-eps (||), matching\n  log_pdf_cloud_parameters_mass. A single non-positive input otherwise\n  yields a negative/Inf Dr_mean that slips past iszero(Dr_mean) and makes\n  exponential_quantile throw DomainError. No-op for valid inputs; the\n  limited variant (already clamped) is unchanged.", "sha": "5ae20c3b5acb1310e9e7342abe116437d20ae469"}
